# data-models

Two primary data models form the core of the system:

## Meetings
Importance Score: 90

Key attributes and relationships:
- Meeting content with multi-source transcript support (Teams + Pocket)
- Hierarchical mindmap structure for knowledge organization
- Signal extraction categories (decisions, actions, blockers, risks)
- DIKW pyramid promotion tracking
- Relations to documents and tickets

## Documents
Importance Score: 85

Key attributes and relationships:
- Document version control with change tracking
- Knowledge graph integration for semantic relationships
- Signal categorization matching meeting structure
- Links to related meetings and tickets
- Contextual relevance scoring

## Relationship Structure

1. Meeting-Document Relations
- Bidirectional linking between related content
- Semantic similarity-based auto-linking
- Context preservation across relationships
- Source attribution tracking

2. Knowledge Integration
- DIKW hierarchy implementation
- Cross-referencing between meetings and documents
- Signal evolution tracking
- Merged signal deduplication

3. Workflow Integration
- Sprint alignment tracking
- Test plan relationships
- Implementation status linking
- Deployment phase tracking

